## In-house libraries

We currently provide [java-logging](https://github.com/hmcts/java-logging)
 and [nodejs-logging](https://github.com/hmcts/nodejs-logging) libraries,

They are there to help integrate your application into the logging system and to have
a common default log format and logger choice across the program.

## Application Insights (App Insights)

We use [Azure Application Insights](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-monitor/app/app-insights-overview)
for storing logs, request tracing, performance analysis, alerting.

### Java

The [ApplicationInsights-Java](https://github.com/microsoft/ApplicationInsights-Java/) 
spring boot starter is used (java-logging depends on it already).

A Java agent is also required, our [docker images](TODO) handle fetching the agent and configuring
the required Java VM flags for it to be used, 

Our current configuration sends all INFO and above `uk.gov.hmcts` log events to App Insights.

